                            <comment id="116484" author="olivergierke" created="Tue, 9 Jun 2015 13:40:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m surprised to see MVC triggering type conversion if the type created is actually of the target type already. Do you think simply cutting the match if the source type is assignable to the target one is enough? If you create a local copy of &lt;tt&gt;DomainClassConverter&lt;/tt&gt; and add that tiny guard:&lt;/p&gt;

